                  </hi>. I live in Long-acre. On the 26th of January, between five and six o'clock in the evening, I was on Ludgate-hill, in company with my brother, and was attracted by a noise—I looked over my brother's shoulder, and saw his handkerchief passing between two lads—the prisoner was one—which of them had hold of it I could not say then, but I seized the prisoner with one hand, and the handkerchief with the other—it was then in his hand—he fell on his knees, and begged me to let him go.</p>
